               <p>I was at my master's door, who is the prosecutor; he lives in <placeName id="t17900424-78-crimeloc419">Rosemary-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17900424-78-crimeloc419" type="placeName" value="Rosemary-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17900424-78-crimeloc419" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17900424-78-off417 t17900424-78-crimeloc419"></join>: I went across the way; my back was towards the shop; I was informed by a gentleman, and I turned round and missed a pair of velveret breeches, lined with leather, from the door; they hung at the door; they were my master's property; I turned round and saw the prisoner on the run, tucking something under his coat; I pursued him, and cried out stop thief! because he ran faster; he was stopped by 
               <persName id="t17900424-78-person716">
                  Arthur
                   Leary
               <interp inst="t17900424-78-person716" type="surname" value="Leary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900424-78-person716" type="given" value="Arthur"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900424-78-person716" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; I saw him drop the breeches before I came up to him.</p>
               <p>(Produced and deposed to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I am an American born; I have no friends.</p>
